BURSTER: Psionic pyrokinetic mutant human

Bursters are psionic mutant humans who manifest pyrokinesis: the power
to create, project, and control fire using only the power of the mind.
They are not trained mages, they were born this way, and their power
emerged in childhood, usually with traumatic results.  On Rifts Earth,
a Burster who learns to control their gift is a formidable ally and a
terrifying enemy.

ATTRIBUTES (APPROXIMATE RANGES)
  IQ: 3-18   ME: 5-20   MA: 3-18   PS: 3-18
  PP: 3-18   PE: 3-18   PB: 3-18   Spd: 3-18

DAMAGE POOL
  SDC: 1d4 x10 + PE (approx 10-40 + PE)

SPECIAL ABILITIES
  - Pyrokinesis: project fire bolts, create flame walls, ignite objects
  - Control existing fire: reshape, suppress, or amplify fires
  - Immunity to fire and heat from psionic origin
  - Enhanced ME attribute

PENALTIES
  - Not OCC eligible, pyrokinetic power defines the character
  - Emotional instability: fire powers may activate involuntarily under
    stress
  - Hunted by Coalition as a psionic threat
  - Normal fire (non-psionic) does still affect the Burster

OCC ELIGIBLE: No.
ALIGNMENT: Any.

